Majesty.Language:
//Buildings - New building costs are reduced by 5 percent[newline][newline]- Heroes may purchase upgraded weapons and armor at this Blacksmith [color:DDBB44][newline][newline]Upgrading this Blacksmith will add:[newline]+ Increased building hit points [newline]+ Higher grade weapons and armor[/color][color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Blacksmith earns revenue every 45 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+30)[newline]* Level 2 Palace Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 3 Palace Gold (+50)[newline]* Each extra Blacksmith (+4)[newline]* Each House (+1)[newline]* Each Manor (+3)[newline]* Each Level 1 Weapon Purchased (+2)[newline]* Each Level 1 Armor Purchased (+3)[newline]* Each Dwarven Settlement (+35%)[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]The smiths of Ardania are all members of the Brotherhood of the Forge. The Brotherhood maintains strict standards that each smithy must meet in their shops.[/color] - New building costs are reduced by 5 percent[newline][newline]- New building foundations start with +3% of their Max HP per level 2 or greater Blacksmith [newline][newline]- Heroes may now purchase advanced weapons and armor [color:DDBB44][newline][newline]Upgrading this Blacksmith will add:[newline]+ Increased building hit points [newline]+ Higher grade weapons and armor[/color][color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Blacksmith earns revenue every 32.5 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+50)[newline]* Level 2 Palace Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 3 Palace Gold (+50)[newline]* Each extra Blacksmith (+4)[newline]* Each House (+1)[newline]* Each Manor (+3)[newline]* Each Level 1 Weapon Purchased (+2)[newline]* Each Level 1 Armor Purchased (+3)[newline]* Each Level 2 Weapon Purchased (+3)[newline]* Each Level 2 Armor Purchased (+6)[newline]* Each Dwarven Settlement (+35%)[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]A veteran smith from Volencia joined the local smithy. His reputation speaks of superior quality arms and armor.[/color] - New building costs are reduced by 5 percent[newline][newline]- New building foundations start with +3% of their Max HP per level 2 or greater Blacksmith[newline][newline]- New buildings gain +2% Max HP per level 3 Blacksmith [newline][newline]- Heroes may now purchase weapons and armor of exceptional quality [color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Blacksmith earns revenue every 20 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+70)[newline]* Level 2 Palace Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 3 Palace Gold (+50)[newline]* Each extra Blacksmith (+4)[newline]* Each House (+1)[newline]* Each Manor (+3)[newline]* Each Level 1 Weapon Purchased (+2)[newline]* Each Level 1 Armor Purchased (+3)[newline]* Each Level 2 Weapon Purchased (+3)[newline]* Each Level 2 Armor Purchased (+6)[newline]* Each Level 3 Weapon Purchased (+1%)[newline]* Each Level 3 Armor Purchased (+2%)[newline]* Each Dwarven Settlement (+35%)[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]Your smith has learned the first secret of Dwarven Steel. This is the pinnacle achievement of any Human smith.[/color] - All research costs are reduced by 5 percent.[newline][newline]- Teaches heroes powerful spells[newline][newline]- Increases the intelligence of newly created heroes in your kingdom[color:DDBB44][newline][newline]Upgrading this Library will add:[newline]+ Increased building hit points [newline]+ Spells of greater power for heroes [newline]+ Increased revenue rate[/color][color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Library earns revenue every 50 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 2 Palace Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 3 Palace Gold (+50)[newline]* Each extra Library (+6)[newline]* Each Arcane Spire (+14)[newline]* Each Hero Visit (+4)[newline]* Each Level 1 Enchantment Purchased (+3)[newline]* Each Level 2 Enchantment Purchased (+4)[newline]* Each Level 3 Enchantment Purchased (+5, +1%)[newline]* Each Manor (+2)[newline]* Each Estate (+10, +3% amount, +2% rate)[newline]* 4% of the total Intelligence of your Heroes and Henchmen as increases revenue[newline]* 1% of the total Intelligence of your Heroes and Henchmen as increases revenue rate[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]A vault of knowledge both mundane and arcane, Libraries are a requisite for any truly enlightened settlement.[/color] - All research costs are reduced by 5 percent.[newline][newline]- Teaches heroes powerful spells[newline][newline]- Increases the intelligence of newly created heroes in your kingdom[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Library earns revenue every 30 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+40)[newline]* Level 2 Palace Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 3 Palace Gold (+50)[newline]* Each extra Library (+6)[newline]* Each Arcane Spire (+14)[newline]* Each Hero Visit (+4)[newline]* Each Level 1 Enchantment Purchased (+3)[newline]* Each Level 2 Enchantment Purchased (+4)[newline]* Each Level 3 Enchantment Purchased (+5, +1%)[newline]* Each Manor (+2)[newline]* Each Estate (+10, +3% amount, +2% rate)[newline]* 4% of the total Intelligence of your Heroes and Henchmen as increases revenue[newline]* 1% of the total Intelligence of your Heroes and Henchmen as increases revenue rate[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]This developed Library features an expanded selection of tomes, especially in the area of magic use.[/color] - Gold is generated based on the size of your kingdom and the level of your Palace[newline][newline]- Heroes may purchase healing and mana potions once Healing Potions are researched[newline][newline]- Using Market Day will generate extra gold, but will require the Marketplace to close for a short time[color:DDBB44][newline][newline]Upgrading this Marketplace will add:[newline]+ Increased building hit points [newline]+ Will generate gold more rapidly [newline]+ Allows research of Rings of Protection[/color][color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Marketplace earns revenue every 30 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+100)[newline]* Level 2 Palace Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 3 Palace Gold (+75)[newline]* Each extra Marketplace (+3)[newline]* Each Trading Post (+6)[newline]* Each House (+2)[newline]* Each Manor (+4)[newline]* Each Elven Bungalow (+20%)[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]Marketplaces are the building blocks of any successful economy, making a significant contribution to your overall income. A wise sovereign will have them constructed in accessible but well defended locations.[/color] - A higher amount of gold is generated based on the size of your kingdom and the level of your Palace[newline][newline]- Heroes may purchase Rings of Protection, once they are researched[newline][newline]- Using Market Day will generate extra gold, but will require the Marketplace to close for a short time[color:DDBB44][newline][newline]Upgrading this Marketplace will add:[newline]+ Increased building hit points [newline]+ Will generate gold more rapidly [newline]+ Allows research of Amulets of Teleportation[/color][color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Marketplace earns revenue every 22.5 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+120)[newline]* Level 2 Palace Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 3 Palace Gold (+75)[newline]* Each extra Marketplace (+3)[newline]* Each Trading Post (+6)[newline]* Each House (+2)[newline]* Each Manor (+4)[newline]* Each Elven Bungalow (+20%)[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]This Marketplace features a greater variety of stores, leading to more business and greater taxable income.[/color] - The highest amount of gold is generated based on the size of your kingdom and the level of your Palace[newline][newline]- Heroes may purchase Amulets of Teleportation, once they are researched[newline][newline]- Using Market Day will generate extra gold, but will require the Marketplace to close for a short time[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Marketplace earns revenue every 15 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+140)[newline]* Level 2 Palace Gold (+25)[newline]* Level 3 Palace Gold (+75)[newline]* Each extra Marketplace (+3)[newline]* Each Trading Post (+6)[newline]* Each House (+2)[newline]* Each Manor (+4)[newline]* Each Elven Bungalow (+20%)[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]This fully developed Marketplace gives you the highest profit. Its expanded size provides office space for high level merchants, as well as being a social center for the community.[/color] - An extra Tax Collector has been enlisted to your service[newline][newline]- Increases the amount of gold carried by Caravans by 15%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]Visible enhancements to your settlement, such as fountains, allow more Tax Collectors to make rounds without upsetting your populace. Your subjects see that taxes are being used to better your settlement.[/color] - Heroes may meditate in the Royal Gardens may gain a beneficial enchantment[newline][newline]- Gold is generated from the stock of rare flowers and herbs[newline][newline]- Increases the loyalty of your heroes[newline][newline]- Enlists an extra Palace Guard and Royal Archer to your kingdom[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Royal Gardens earns revenue every 27 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+60)[newline][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]Landscape from the Eastern Provinces are renowned for their creative and uplifting garden designs. These beautiful plots provide rest and inspiration to weary heroes as they return to town.[/color] - Statues raise the loyalty of heroes in your kingdom[newline][newline]- Increases the quality of Henchmen in your kingdom[newline][newline]- Enlists an extra Peasant to your kingdom[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]Assured that their deeds will not go unrecognized, your heroes strive to complete their quests with renewed vigor determination.[/color] - Recruits Dwarves[newline][newline]- Auto- fires ballista bolts at nearby enemies[newline][newline]- Allows additional Ballista Towers to be built.[newline][newline]- Increases the amount of gold generated by your Blacksmiths by 35% for each Settlement[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]The Dwarven engineers of Dtar- Mordin devised the complex mechanisms that automate this outpost. Dwarven knowledge of mechanics and metallurgy is unparalled in all of Ardania.[/color] - Recruits Elves[newline][newline]- Increases the amount of gold generated by your Marketplaces by 20% for each Bungalow[newline][newline]- An Elven Lounge will soon be built in any kingdom containing an Elven Bungalow[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline][newline]Prone to self- indulgence, Elves require a lavish dwelling when they settle in any kingdom. Bright blue shingles are a characteristic of all Elven structures and date back to pre- recorded times.[/color]
- Increases the overall Intelligence of heroes and henchmen[newline][newline]- Each Spire unlocks spells and abilities for your henchmen to use.[newline][newline]- Each spire unlocks one generic spell and one class specific spell for heroes to learn from the Library.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Arcane Spires are manifestly made of highly concentrated magic. Erected by cabals of spellcasters, these spires are common amongst kingdoms specializing in the arcane arts. Though their presence is unnerving to commoners, those who are specially attuned to the mystical forces of Ardania find themselves inextricably drawn towards these fonts of magical energy.[/color] - Provides a place for Heroes to convert 100% their untaxed gold to stored gold[newline][newline]- Heroes with an account will automatically have all their newly obtained gold converted to stored gold[newline][newline]- Grants heroes with an account an interest rate of 1% of their total gold each revenue cycle of their primary Bank[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Bank earns revenue every 60 seconds adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+100)[newline]* Total Account Gold (+1% of All Account Gold of This Bank)[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]A safe haven for the bounties acquired by your heroes, Banks offer an alternative for heroes to develop their own stores of gold rather than offer them up to the coffers of their Guildhouses.[/color] - Increases the overall Wisdom of heroes[newline][newline]- Generates an Inspiration point every 8 seconds and can hold up to 20 Inspiration points at a time.[newline][newline]- Heroes can visit the Shrine to obtain half of its currently held Inspiration points.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]In places where worship of the Ardanian gods is paramount, structures such as these can be found to offer such services. Although heroes can gather for such activities in their respective Temples, Shrines provide an ideal, neutral place for any individual to offer prayer to whichever god they choose.[/color] - Generates gold at a greater rate than houses and generates extra gold based on the number of living henchmen and heroes in your kingdom for your Tax Collectors to gather.[newline][newline]- Manors are built for every two Houses.[newline][newline]- Provides an additional point of HP for all of your henchmen.[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Manor earns revenue at the same rate as the Palace adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+12)[newline]* Gold Per Hero (+1 Gold up to a maximum of +20)[newline]* Gold Per 2 Henchmen (+1 Gold up to a maximum of +12)[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Manors are the first signs of a kingdom entering prosperous times. As a kingdom thrives, the distinction between different classes of living become more apparent as wealthier families construct lodgings fit for people of their status.[/color] - Generates gold at a greater rate than manors and generates extra gold based on the number of living henchmen and heroes in your kingdom for your Tax Collectors to gather.[newline][newline]- Estates are built for every two Houses and two Manors.[newline][newline]- Estates provide an extra point to the Primary Attribute for all of your heroes.[newline][newline]- Heroes with enough Prestige can visit an estate for an audience with a noble.[newline][newline]- Estates provide a Mercenary Arbalest henchman to defend your kingdom.[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]This Estate earns revenue at the same rate as the Palace adding:[newline]* Base Gold (+20)[newline]* Gold Per Hero (+2 Gold)[newline]* Gold Per Henchmen (+1 Gold)[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Estates house the nobles and lords of your kingdom. Men and women of status and influence commission such structures to establish their foothold in sovereign territory. These structures are an inspiring sight to heroes who seek a luxurious life after their adventuring days are over.[/color]
//Lairs - Appears in place of Sewers after many henchmen have died.[newline][newline]- Spawns warped versions of your fallen henchmen to attack your kingdom.[newline][newline]- Increases number and rate of spawns based on number of dead henchmen in the pit.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Heroes receive burials, Tax Collectors are cremated in the Palace and lost Caravans are left in the wilds. But what of the others conscripted into service for their kingdom? Evidently, their final resting place was alongside the wastes of civilization. An altar to an unknown and malicious deity, these pits don a sinister presence when supplied with enough offerings to entice its endless appetite for more sacrifices.[/color]
//Henchmen - Assigned to a Guardhouse.[newline][newline]- Defends your settlement against invaders.[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]5 - 6 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 3[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 5%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These men-at-arms patrol the area around their assigned Guardhouse. They also guard construction sites against opportunistic raiders. They are often tough loners who enjoy the quiet of outpost life.[/color] - Assigned to a Guardhouse.[newline][newline]- Defends your settlement against invaders.[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]5 - 7 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Archers patrol the area around their assigned Guardhouses. They also guard construction sites against threats. They grant ranged support to their melee-inclined companions.[/color] - Assigned to a Guardhouse.[newline][newline]- Defends your settlement against invaders.[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]5 - 7 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 5%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 10%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Veteran Guards patrol the area around their assigned Guardhouses. They also guard construction sites against threats. Years of experience mark these rugged soldiers as tough defenders.[/color] - Defends your settlement against invaders.[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]5 - 7 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 5[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 5%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 10%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These elite guards defend the palace. They also patrol around construction sites, guarding against opportunistics raiders. A strong sense of brotherhood often binds these seasoned troops.[/color]
- Ranged henchman that patrols the buildings of your kingdom.[newline][newline]- Can use the Healing Salve ability if your kingdom has at least one Arcane Spire.[newline][newline]- Can use the Split Shot ability if your kingdom has at least three Arcane Spires.[color:DDBB44][newline][newline]+Healing Salve - Heals this henchman's HP by an amount equal to his Intelligence.[newline][newline]+Split Shot - Allows this henchman to attack an additional target every two seconds.[/color][newline][newline]Attack:[newline]5 - 7 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Guards with a keen eye and unquestionable loyalty, these archers are a godsend to commoners for their tireless patrol of even the most hazardous locations to defend the holdings of their kingdom.[/color] - Long- ranged sniper that patrols Manors, Estates and Marketplaces.[newline][newline]- Can critically strike targets if your kingdom has at least one Arcane Spire.[newline][newline]- Can use the Volley ability if your kingdom has at least three Arcane Spires.[color:DDBB44][newline][newline]+Volley - Increases this henchman's attack speed greatly for a short time.[/color][newline][newline]Attack:[newline]8 - 12 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 1[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Coin is the only patron that these shrewd "businessmen" will provide their services to. Despite their unsavory reputation, their capabilities of ending most common threats to the kingdom in a single shot is a testament to their effectiveness.[/color] - Skilled melee combatant that patrols the Palace, Guardhouses and Warriors Guilds.[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]7 - 8 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 8[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 15%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Exemplary swordsmen one and all, Squires are capable of standing toe- to- toe dauntlessly with even the fiercest opponents. Such henchman are only capable of being trained to full effectiveness by a highly skilled Warrior.[/color] - Support henchman that patrols Libraries, Arcane Spires, Temples to Krypta, Wizards Guilds and Wizards Towers.[newline][newline]- Starts with the Corrosion Ball ability as a basic attack.[newline][newline]- Can use the Enchant Wizard Tower ability if your kingdom has at least one Arcane Spire.[newline][newline]- Can use the Etherealize ability if your kingdom has at least two Arcane Spires.[newline][newline]- Can use the Acid Fog ability if your kingdom has at least three Arcane Spires.[color:DDBB44][newline][newline]+Corrosion Ball - Deals spell damage and reduces target armor with each shot.[newline][newline]+Enchant Wizard Tower - Enchants a nearby Wizards Tower during combat, enhancing it's damage, range and duration enchanted based on the Mage's Intelligence.[newline][newline]+Etherealize - Turns the target Ethereal, reducing its movement, attack speed and magic resistance based on the Mage's Intelligence.[newline][newline]+Acid Fog - Engulfs an area in a fog of acid, dealing minor spell damage and reducing the max HP of enemies over time.[/color][newline][newline]Attack:[newline]6 - 8 [color:18E50D]Poison[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Magical: 3[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 15%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 30%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 15%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Scholars who have dedicated their lives to understanding the mystic arts. Sponsored by the sovereign, these practitioners of magic apply their knowledge through more practical means with their versatile array of spells.[/color]
//Monsters - Powerful combatants[newline][newline]- Difficult to locate, they do not appear on the mini-map[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 15 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -25%[newline][color:982828]Chaotic:[/color] 20%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 30%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 20%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 30%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These ancient tree spirits hark back to the time of the World Birthing, before Man walked the land now called Ardania. They despise Humans, whom they see as tree killers slashing and burning away the forests of the world.[/color] - Breathes fire on opponents from a range[newline][newline]- Extremely powerful opponent[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]18 - 21 [color:E8210B]Fire[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 6[newline]Magical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] 90%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 60%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 30%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 25%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 25%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Ardanian dragons seldom stir from their underground nests. May Dauros have mercy on the Sovereign who stirs them from their extended slumber.[/color] - Average skill melee combat[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]4 - 6 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Magical: 2[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 10%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 25%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] -20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These woodland spirits pass over from the realm of Fey to pursue their unknown agendas. They prey on humans who wander too close to their woodland lairs.[/color] - Casts spells of Paralyzation and Destruction[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]16 - 22 [color:1BAEDB]Electric[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline]Magical: 6[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] 20%[newline][color:1BAEDB]Electric:[/color] 40%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 50%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Creatures of unknown origin, Oculi are a relatively new menace to Ardania. Some Tholarian scholars believe they are somehow related to Dragons.[/color] - Remains stationary[newline][newline]- Difficult to locate, they do not appear on the mini-map[newline][newline]- Fires poisonous spores[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]4 - 5 [color:18E50D]Poison[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -10%[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] -33%[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 65%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] -33%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]A twisted strain of plant life resulting from the misguided magics of Pyrog the Shadowed, it is rumored that multiple Strangleweeds in a small vicinity share a collective, almost animal intelligence.[/color] - Will appear in any developing communities[newline][newline]- Creates a nuisance in your settlements by random attacks[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]1 - 1 [color:18E50D]Poison[/color][newline]1 - 2 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Rats are present in all the kingdoms of Ardania. It is rumored that they are spies for their larger bipedal cousins, the Ratmen.[/color] - Quickly surround their opponents in melee combat[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]3 - 4 [color:18E50D]Poison[/color][newline]1 - 3 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 50%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] -30%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] -20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These deadly arachnids are said to have been selectively bred by the Grisnot tribe of goblins. Intended to be guard beasts, these spiders swiftly devoured their would be masters as they slept.[/color] - Lends missile attacks to their warband[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]3 - 4 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Goblin Archers are crude hunters wielding poorly crafted bows designed to launch crude but heavy arrows.[/color] - Skilled melee combatant[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]2 - 3 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline]1 - 4 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 10%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 15%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 15%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Veteran fighters, these elite Goblins wielrd two weapons at a time, wading into their opponents.[/color] - Will band together attacking in large numbers[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]3 - 4 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 1[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Goblin Fighters are the weakest of the Goblin troops you will face. Be careful when estimating the danger they pose, for they may quickly form a powerful warband.[/color] - Summons magical swarms of insects to attack their foes[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]9 - 11 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Magical: 1[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These unholy Goblins worship Grum-Gog, the Lord of Pestilence. They seek the destruction of Ardania through a plague of insects.[/color] - Motivated by greed[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]6 - 9 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 1[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 10%[newline][color:1BAEDB]Electric:[/color] 5%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These foul abominations are the spawn of Scrylia the Serpent Queen. Ultimately the Harpies rebelled against their dark mistress, striking down her vast empire from within.[/color] - Very strong melee combatant[newline][newline]- Avoids kingdom settlements where possible[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]7 - 8 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 30%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 10%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Foul tempered and malicious, Hellbears savagely attack any heroes who stray too close to their lairs. The remnants of their many victims are strewn about their dens.[/color] - Skilled in melee combat[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]1 - 2 [color:18E50D]Poison[/color][newline]3 - 5 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 1[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 25%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 35%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These abominations formed the core of Scrylia the Serpent Queen's dreaded legions. They joined the Harpies in their rebellion against the Serpent Queen, ending her reign of terror.[/color] - Strong melee combatants[newline][newline]- Constantly seek battle against kingdom settlements and heroes[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]7 - 10 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 15%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 20%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 15%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Minotaurs are a twisted breed of warrior. It is rumored they were created by the sorcerer, Andravus, to serve in his army as shock troops. They were instrumental in the conquest of Lormidia in the year K.A.1412.[/color] - Average skill in melee combat[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]4 - 5 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 1[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 25%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 5%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 5%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Ratmen are greedy theives, leaping forth from sewer entrances to waylay Tax Collectors or raid unsuspecting settlements. It is theorized that these giant rodents are the result of a magical discharge seeping into the kingdom sewers, mutating the rats that dwell therein. It is rumored that they stem from a central warren with a population rivaling the greatest cities of Ardania.[/color] - Weak combatant[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]2 - 4 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 5%[newline][color:1BAEDB]Electric:[/color] 10%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These malignant birds are twisted, evil parodies of the noble Ardanian Eagle. They prey on the weak and infirm.[/color] - Extremely strong melee combatant[newline][newline]- Likes to destroy buildings[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]24 - 27 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 10[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] 33%[newline][color:1BAEDB]Electric:[/color] 25%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 10%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 30%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 55%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Spirits similar to the Daemonwood, these stone titans relentlessly attack settlements. They can never be truly destroyed. When their bodies crumble their spirit is released to animate a new body of stone.[/color] - Attacks by spewing acid at their opponents from a range[newline][newline]- Often summoned to guard evil lairs in the wilderness[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]3 - 5 [color:7C34B0]Necrotic[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 30%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 10%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Similar to some insects, Rust Spitters dissolve their food externally with their acidic projectiles before consuming it. They are extremely territorial and rarely encountered in groupings of less than three.[/color] - Weak melee combatant[newline][newline]- Resistant to attacks by missile weapons[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]6 - 7 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 35%[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -50%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 40%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 75%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]These animated bones are raised through necromantic spells of dark origin. When the ether winds of Ardania blow with great strength, recently fallen heroes may arise from graveyards within your kingdom.[/color] - Attracted to active Marketplaces and Trading Posts[newline][newline]- Will regenerate any damage they have sustainted[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]9 - 11 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 3[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -10%[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] -30%[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 45%[newline][color:982828]Chaotic:[/color] 40%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 20%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 20%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Little is known of troll ecology. It is theorized that their regenerative process is also their method of reproduction. This would explain the remarkable similarity of all specimens encountered.[/color] - May attack in melee combat or cast life draining spells[newline][newline]- Life draining attack heals wounds they have sustainted[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]10 - 12 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 1[newline]Magical: 3[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -50%[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 35%[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -25%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 40%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Vampires are the most feared of all the common undead. It is believed they were created by an evil sorcerer's experiments in extending his own life by draining blood from the living.[/color] - Will avoid kingdom buildings where possible[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]6 - 8 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 30%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 5%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Vargs are cunning and evil. They hae their own guttural language for communicating their dire plots to the rest of their pack.[/color] - Relentlessly hunt any heroes they encounter[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]7 - 9 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 1[newline]Magical: 1[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 15%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 25%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Werewolves are a hybrid creature resulting from either a Human or Varg infected with a lycanthropic disease. Their continuous pain and rage drive them into a homicidal mania.[/color] - Weak melee combatant[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]5 - 7 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 1[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -50%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 30%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Zombies are animated corpses still in an early state of decay. When the ether winds of Ardania blow with great strength, recently fallen heroes may arise from graveyards within your kingdom.[/color]
- Casts powerful spells of mass destruction[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 17 [color:EAEA19]Necrotic[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline]Magical: 5[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 20%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 35%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 50%[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -40%[newline][newline]Powerful sorcerers often place these dread specters as guardians. Of the heroes who have faced a Black Phantom, few have survived.[/color] - May attack at a range with fiery blasts[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 15 [color:E8210B]Fire[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline]Magical: 2[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] 80%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 30%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 10%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 10%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 25%[newline][newline]This three-headed guardian of the nether regions often enters Ardania, enslaving those he encounters in horrific dungeon like pits. Legends tell that he draws strength from the suffering he inflicts.[/color] - Extremely strong in melee combat[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]31 - 40 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 65%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 25%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 15%[newline][newline]This wandering behemoth seeks revenge on the hero who so cruelly blinded him many years ago in his island cave.[/color] Attack:[newline]19 - 25 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 7[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 10%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 40%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 25%[newline][newline]Rrongol is a fearful predator, stalking Ardania's wilderness with ravenous zeal. Woe to the heroes who cross his track in the wildlands.[/color] - Possesses many powerful spells[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]16 - 24 [color:7C34B0]Necrotic[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline]Magical: 15[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -25%[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 40%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 25%[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -35%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 90%[newline][newline]Once a high priestess of Krypta, the Liche Queen is now the sworn enemy of all things living. Her undead minions are a considerable threat to any that settle too close to her lair.[/color] - Can summon dark creatures to do his bidding[newline][newline]- Has knowledge of many spells both offensive and defensive[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]13 - 20 [color:18E50D]Poison[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Magical: 8[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 70%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 60%[newline][newline]A master of dark magic, the Witch King is a terrible foe for any sovereign. Having extended his life through dark sorcery, he is now centuries old. It was he who threatened the destruction of Ravenswood in northern Ardania K.A.[/color] - Breathes a destructive gout of flame at opponents[newline][newline]- Invulnerable to many weapons and attacks[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 15 [color:E8210B]Fire[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 10[newline]Magical: 7[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] 90%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 25%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 40%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 35%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 35%[newline][newline]Vendral, the two-headed dragon of Grimspire, is thought to be little more than an ancient myth. The frontier around the Hellfire Mountains, known to the locals as the Mountains of Doom, has been settled for nearly a century. Expeditions into the heart of the mountainous range began this spring. The heroes undertaking this quest have yet to return with word of their adventures.[/color] - Uses the spells Terrify, Mind Warp, and Horrify[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]26 - 39 [color:982828]Chaotic[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 8[newline]Magical: 17[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 40%[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -45%[newline][color:982828]Chaotic:[/color] 90%[newline][newline]This creature had only existed as scattered, unreliable rumors until your expedition to the Northern Reaches. Its origin is uncertain, but some believe it to be the final, and fatal, creation of the vile mage Pyrog the Shadowed. The Abomination is remarkably stealthy for its size. Its magical wake often stuns any nearby small animals, birds, or insects, leaving them littering the ground behind it.[/color] - Can cast Strengthen Shadow Beasts[newline][newline]- Will resurrect unless Stones is also killed[newline][newline]- Her resurrection will release Chain Lightning that damages any foes nearby[newline][newline]- Can cast Recall for aid from Stones[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]17 - 21 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 7[newline]Magical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:1BAEDB]Electric:[/color] 33%[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 55%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 60%[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -50%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 5%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 50%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 20%[newline][newline]Styx is the female half of the legendary evil wights, Styx and Stones. In her mortal incarnation, Styx was a brutal warrior queen of the now exterminated Tundra Giants. Many who faced her in battle chose to take their own lives instead of submitting to her inhumane interrogation.[/color] - Can cast Strengthen Shadow Beasts[newline][newline]- Will resurrect unless Styx is also killed[newline][newline]- Her resurrection will release Chain Lightning that damages any foes nearby[newline][newline]- Can cast Recall for aid from Styx[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]17 - 21 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 7[newline]Magical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:1BAEDB]Electric:[/color] 33%[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 55%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 60%[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -50%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 5%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 50%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 20%[newline][newline]Stones served as Styx's coldly efficient General in their mortal days. Severely outnumbered, he and Styx died together in battle on the Zhizhik Flats. The Witch King recognized their potential as a terrifying force. He brought the two into the world of the unliving in order to serve him. After the Witch King's death, the pair of wights remained in the desolate north, away from the Ardanian heartlands.[/color] - High combat stats, for a Goblin[newline][newline]- Highly intelligent, for a Goblin[newline][newline]- Protects Goblin lairs[newline][newline]- Aids in concentrated attacks[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]6 - 11 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 20%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 25%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 25%[newline][newline]In the Goblin military hierarchy, Overlords sit at the peak. Unlike Goblin Champions whose position is based solely on strength, Overlords must also show unusually high cunning. Most Overlords start their career as Champions, with only a few who demonstrate the required ingenuity rising to the next rank.[/color] - Impressive armor[newline][newline]- Often leads raiding parties[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 14 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 6[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 40%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 10%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 20%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 25%[newline][newline]These massive beasts are the elite soldiers of the Rat King. They lead the pack in every way. They池e the best fighters, the biggest eaters, and the most thorough groomers. Most other Ratmen couldn稚 even walk under the Champions heavy field gear, let alone swing a blade with the same deadly efficiency.[/color] - Wields spell Damage Shield[newline][newline]- Can cast Plague[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 15 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Magical: 3[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 30%[newline][newline]Only the most wily and skilled she-rats can rise to the Shamaness position. Ratman Shamanesses employ their magical abilities to enhance their compatriots during an attack. The ornately dressed Shamanesses are among the most revered of Ratkind, due to their uncommon skills.[/color] - Does heavy damage by hurling an explosive round[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 22 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 95%[newline][newline]The Ratmen have built rickety siege engines down in the sewers and wheel them to the surface to aid in their conquest. The Ratapult is controlled by a small driver and launches Balefire, an explosive, magical projectile. Rhoden himself invented the device.[/color] - Unusually fast[newline][newline]- Powerful attacks[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]9 - 11 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline]2 - 3 [color:EAEA19]Necrotic[/color][newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 33%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 5%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 15%[newline][newline]Hard to detect, these undead beasts can swiftly pounce on their prey with little warning. Their teeth and claws are unusually dense, allowing them to rip through armor plate. While their vicious nature would seem to put taming them out of the question, some have reported seeing Shadow Beasts as minions of various supernatural evils.[/color] - Casts spell Petrify[newline][newline]- Casts spell Summon Medusa[newline][newline]- Casts spell Medusa Enchantment[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 15 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -25%[newline][newline]During the Serpent Queen's attempted Ardanian conquest, the Greater Gorgons served as the lieutenants of her forces. Ultimately, this led to the destruction from within of the Serpent Queen's army when the Medusae refused to be subordinate to the Gorgons. A few Gorgons escaped the resulting bloodshed, fleeing to the Northern Reaches where they honed their magics to better bring the Medusae under their control.[/color] - Breathes freezing ice blast[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 15 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -25%[newline][newline]Dwelling in glacial caves, Ice Dragons are just as rare - and as deadly - as their southern cousins. In the time of the Dragon King, it's said the ancient Dragon, Shallevex, turned an entire army to ice within minutes. The icy devastation of that day led the locals to name a nearby, rock-studded area Shallevex's Conquest.[/color] - Can teleport over short distances[newline][newline]- Very quick reflexes[newline][newline]- Incredibly strong[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]23 - 26 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 7[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -40%[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 60%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 20%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 40%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 40%[newline][newline]Little is known of this rare northern creature for few have ever been seen. It is conjectured by some sages that they are relatives of the larger Yeti, as their appearance and habitat are similar, however, the Wendigo's odd blinking ability lends to some theories of the creature having been created magically. The only thing certain regarding the beast is that it can be lethal to get too close to it![/color] - Incredibly strong[newline][newline]- Fast and intelligent[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]14 - 17 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline]6 - 8 [color:0B25E8]Cold[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 7[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] -40%[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 60%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 20%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 40%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 40%[newline][newline]One of the deadliest creatures of the Northlands, the massive Yeti is a formidable match for even a small group of competent heroes. Their icy fists can crush plate armor like paper. Their pungent smell is a hero's best defense. When you smell a Yeti, prepare yourself for a tough fight - or run.[/color]
- Relentlessly attacks and destroys the buildings of your kingdom[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -30%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]With vacant, empty eyes and a body drenched in congealed blood, one would come to the natural conclusion that Krypta's influence was involved. The Priestesses attest that these things are not truly dead nor are they alive, yet they remain outside the domain of Krypta. Whatever loyalties these peasants had in life has been twisted and inverted in whatever existence they reside in now.[/color] - Relentlessly attacks your kingdom[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]5 - 7 [color:7C34B0]Necrotic[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Magical: 5[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 15%[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -30%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 50%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]With vacant, empty eyes and a body drenched in congealed blood, one would come to the natural conclusion that Krypta's influence was involved. The Priestesses attest that these things are not truly dead nor are they alive, yet they remain outside the domain of Krypta. Whatever loyalties these soldiers had in life has been twisted and inverted in whatever existence they reside in now.[/color] - Relentlessly attacks your kingdom[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]1 - 1 [color:7C34B0]Necrotic[/color][newline]7 - 8 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 3[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -30%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]With vacant, empty eyes and a body drenched in congealed blood, one would come to the natural conclusion that Krypta's influence was involved. The Priestesses attest that these things are not truly dead nor are they alive, yet they remain outside the domain of Krypta. Whatever loyalties these soldiers had in life has been twisted and inverted in whatever existence they reside in now.[/color] - Relentlessly attacks your kingdom[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]1 - 1 [color:7C34B0]Necrotic[/color][newline]6 - 8 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 4[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -30%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 20%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 10%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]With vacant, empty eyes and a body drenched in congealed blood, one would come to the natural conclusion that Krypta's influence was involved. The Priestesses attest that these things are not truly dead nor are they alive, yet they remain outside the domain of Krypta. Whatever loyalties these soldiers had in life has been twisted and inverted in whatever existence they reside in now.[/color] - Relentlessly attacks your kingdom[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]1 - 1 [color:7C34B0]Necrotic[/color][newline]11 - 14 [color:666462]Piercing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -30%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 20%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]With vacant, empty eyes and a body drenched in congealed blood, one would come to the natural conclusion that Krypta's influence was involved. The Priestesses attest that these things are not truly dead nor are they alive, yet they remain outside the domain of Krypta. Whatever loyalties these soldiers had in life has been twisted and inverted in whatever existence they reside in now.[/color] - Relentlessly attacks your kingdom[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]1 - 1 [color:7C34B0]Necrotic[/color][newline]8 - 9 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 9[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:EAEA19]Divine:[/color] -30%[newline][color:7C34B0]Necrotic:[/color] 20%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 5%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 25%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 40%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]With vacant, empty eyes and a body drenched in congealed blood, one would come to the natural conclusion that Krypta's influence was involved. The Priestesses attest that these things are not truly dead nor are they alive, yet they remain outside the domain of Krypta. Whatever loyalties these soldiers had in life has been twisted and inverted in whatever existence they reside in now.[/color] - Attracted to active Marketplaces and Trading Posts[newline][newline]- Regenerates damage faster as its max hit points increase over time[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]7 - 8 [color:969593]Crushing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 2[newline]Magical: 1[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:18E50D]Poison:[/color] 50%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] -66%[newline][color:982828]Chaotic:[/color] 75%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 50%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 50%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 50%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Troll ecology is in and of itself scantly understood, so their manifestation as spirits is even more mysterious. Their voracious avarice and regenerative capabilities are exaggerated greatly in this state, and left to their own devices these entities have been the root cause of disastrous calamities in neighboring kingdoms.[/color] - Overwhelming melee combatant[newline][newline]- Constantly seeks battle against kingdom settlements and heroes[newline][newline]- Cleaves through multiple enemies in close combat with each attack[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]12 - 16 [color:ADABA8]Slashing[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Physical: 7[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] 10%[newline][color:0B25E8]Cold:[/color] 25%[newline][color:969593]Crushing:[/color] 30%[newline][color:ADABA8]Slashing:[/color] 25%[newline][color:666462]Piercing:[/color] 10%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Amongst these monstrous beastmen, a hierarchy has arisen within their savage society. Minotaur Lords boast excessive strength, hides with the consistency of stone and are capable of wielding their gargantuan battle axes with ruthless efficiency in wide, sweeping arcs to fell as many of their enemies as they can with minimal effort.[/color] - Casts spells of Paralyzation and Mass Destruction[newline][newline]Attack:[newline]16 - 22 [color:1BAEDB]Electric[/color][newline][newline]Armor:[newline]Magical: 9[newline][newline]Resistances:[newline][color:E8210B]Fire:[/color] 30%[newline][color:1BAEDB]Electric:[/color] 45%[newline][color:ED38AE]Arcane:[/color] 66%[newline][color:982828]Chaotic:[/color] 15%[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Rare, deadly and terrifyingly knowledgeable, Elder Orbs represent the pinnacle of intelligence for the uncivilized monstrosities in the region. Spellcasters covet their eyes for their potent magical properties, yet they behold a piercing stare that retains their owner's sinister gaze even decades after death.[/color]
[color:yellow]This sign contains information regarding the various changes to the Attribute System[/color][newline][newline]- Heroes now gain an attribute point every level and will spend one every other level on their Primary Attribute, and distribute the other one to an attribute of their choice based on preference.[newline][newline]- Attribute points can be generated by Heroes based on their number of Insight Points. Insight Points can be gained in a variety of ways and every 14 Insight Points can be converted to a single Attribute Point.[newline][newline]- Heroes now all have a Mana System governed by Intelligence along with a Mana Regeneration and Health Regeneration system. Heroes will regenerate Mana more quickly when resting.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Artifice: [/color]Each point of Artifice grants 1% Movement Speed and 4% Attack Speed, reduces the cooldown of magic spells and abilities by 0.75% per point of Artifice, and reduces the cooldown of non- magic spells and abilities by 1%.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Intelligence:[/color] Each point of Intelligence increases Maximum Mana by 2, Mana Regeneration rate by 0.04, Mana Potion restoration points by 0.25, increases the duration of magic spells and abilities by 0.8%, reduces the cooldown of magic spells and abilities by 0.5%, increases flat Spell Damage by 0.25, and increases percent Spell Damage by 0.1%.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Strength:[/color] No changes.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Vitality:[/color] Each point of Vitality increases Armor by 0.10, Healing Potions 0.25 more points of healing, and increases Health Regeneration by 0.03.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]Willpower:[/color] Willpower determines the power of effects being received, not being dealt. Each point of Willpower decreases the duration and effective power of Debuffs by 0.5% and increases the duration and effective power of Buffs by 1%.[color:BCBCFF][newline][newline]New Attribute: Wisdom:[/color] Wisdom determines the power of effects being dealt, not being received. Each point of Wisdom increases experience gain by 0.5%, generates one Insight Point per level, increases the effective power of buffs and debuffs by 0.75% and reduces Mana spent on spells by 0.4%. [color:yellow]This sign contains information regarding the various changes to the Spell System[/color][newline][newline]- Most non- expansion spells and newly developed spells use the new spell system that can modify and include new aspects to spells such as duration, cooldown, mana cost, casting range and casting behavior.[newline][newline]- Spells can have varying effects based on Attributes governing certain spells. Willpower, Intelligence, and Wisdom attributes affect spells, specifically buff and debuff spells, the most in terms of effectiveness.[newline][newline]- There is currently one Spell Tree implemented with this system for the Wizard hero only that uses spell Levels, synergy bonuses, Tier bonuses, and pre- requisite spells to unlock new spells further down the tree. [color:yellow]This sign contains detailed information on all Library spells both new and old[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Power Shock:[/color] Deals 20 spell damage to a single target. Cooldown changes from 16 to 5 seconds. Range set to 60% of max cast range. Mana cost set to 4.[color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Flame Shield:[/color] Temporarily raises the armor and magic resistance of a target. Magic Resistance gain changed from 20 to 8 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 6). Armor gain changed from 4 to 1 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 10). Duration changed from 20 to 14 seconds. Cooldown changed from 30 to 12 seconds. Range set to 50% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 6. Can cast on nearby allies. Does not naturally stack. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]New Generic Spell: Regenerate:[/color] Restores health immediately and heals over time. Immediately restores 1 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 6) health. Increases Health Regeneration rate by 0.50 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 8). Duration set to 8 seconds. Cooldown set to 14 seconds. Range set to 50% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 7. Can cast on allies. Does not naturally stack. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]New Wizard Spell: Transmute:[/color] Instantly kills an enemy unit at low Health and converts the remaining HP into Gold and Experience. Target must have less than or equal to 10 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 6)% remaining HP. The remaining HP is multiplied by the Wizard's Intelligence and converted to gold. 66% of the gold conversion is added as experience. Cooldown set to 12.5 seconds. Range set to 67% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 10. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]New Priestess Spell: Wither:[/color] Reduces the movement speed, attack speed and strength of an enemy unit. Decreases movement speed by 60 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color])%. Decreases attack speed by 150 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] * 2)%. Decreases Strength by 3 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 5). Duration set to 8 seconds. Cooldown set to 12 seconds. Range set to 70% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 5. Does not naturally stack. [color:yellow]This sign contains detailed information on all non- Expansion Agrela spells[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Healer's Healing:[/color] Heals an allied unit. Cooldown reduced from 2.4 to 2 seconds. Range set to 50% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 2. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Aura of Peace:[/color] Unchanged. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Meditation:[/color] Increases the dodge, parry and sight of an allied unit. Will pre- emptively cast on the unit the Healer is supporting. Dodge gain changed from 25 to 15 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 5). Parry gain changed from 25 to 15 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 5). Sight gain changed from 50 to 30 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 4). Duration changed from 52 to 33 seconds. Cooldown changed from 55 to 22 seconds. Range set to 50% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 9. Can cast on nearby allies. Does not naturally stack. [color:yellow]This sign contains detailed information on all non- Expansion Dauros spells[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Hands of Steel:[/color] Increases the Monk's Strength and HtoH value. Strength gain changed from 16 to 8 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 5). HtoH value changed from 25 to 12 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 4). Duration changed from 26 to 20 seconds. Cooldown reduced from 29 to 10 seconds. Range set to melee (self). Mana Cost set to 2. Does not stack. Cannot cast on allies. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Stone Skin:[/color] Increases the target's armor. Armor gain changed from 8 to 3 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 7). Duration changed from 33 to 27 seconds. Cooldown changed from 35 to 18 seconds. Range set to 50% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 5. Can cast on allies. Does not naturally stack. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Iron Will:[/color] Increases the magical resistance and critical strike chance of the target. Magic Resistance gain changed from 55 to 35 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 2). Critical Strike chance changed from 6 to 1 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 7). Duration changed from 40 to 32 seconds. Cooldown changed from 42 to 20 seconds. Range set to 50% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 12. Can cast on nearby allies. Does not naturally stack. [color:yellow]This sign contains detailed information on all non- Expansion Fervus spells[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Camouflage:[/color] Makes the Cultist undetectable until he attacks or the duration runs out. Duration changed from 21 to 16 seconds. Cooldown reduced from 13.5 to 8 seconds. Range set to melee (self). Mana Cost set to 5. Does not stack. Cannot cast on allies. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Charm Animal:[/color] Takes control of the target animal, increasing it's attributes based on the Cultist's attributes. Increases the charmed creature's Max HP by [color:BCBCFF]Level[/color] * 2. Increases the charmed creature's Dodge value by [color:BCBCFF]Artifice[/color] / 2. Increases the charmed creature's Attack value by [color:BCBCFF]Artifice[/color] / 3. Increases the charmed creature's Parry value by [color:BCBCFF]Artifice[/color] / 4. Increases the charmed creature's Magic Resistance by [color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 6. Increases the charmed creature's strength by [color:BCBCFF]Strength[/color] / 10. Allows an additional creature to be charmed every 3 levels up to a maximum of 5 creatures. Cooldown changed from 5.3 seconds to 5 seconds. Range set to 67% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 11. Does not naturally stack. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Change Shape:[/color] Transforms the Cultist into a Hellbear, increasing armor, HP, Strength and Vitality. Armor gain changed from 6 to 3 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 8). HP gain changed from 35 to 24 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 5). Strength gain changed from 10 to 6 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 7). Vitality gain changed from 15 to 9 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 6). Duration changed from 26.5 to 20 seconds. Cooldown changed from 56 to 34 seconds. Range set to melee (self). Mana Cost set to 18. Cannot cast on allies. Does not naturally stack. [color:yellow]This sign contains detailed information on all non- Expansion Helia spells[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Solarus Sun Scorch:[/color] Deals 15 + Level Spell damage to all enemy units in a small area. Radius changed from 65 to 50 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 2). Cooldown reduced from 17 seconds to 7 seconds. Range set to 25% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 5. No longer attempts to automatically cast against buildings. [color:yellow]This sign contains detailed information on all non- Expansion Krypta spells[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Drain Life:[/color] Deals 15 Spell damage to the target and restores HP to the Priestess or a minion. Cooldown reduced from 2.5 seconds to 2 seconds. Range set to 67% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 2. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Animate Skeleton:[/color] Creates a skeletal minion from the Priestess and increases it's attributes based on the Priestess's [color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color]. Increases the skeletal minion's Max HP by [color:BCBCFF]Level[/color]. Increases the skeletal minion's Dodge value by [color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 20. Increases the skeletal minion's Sight value by [color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 8. Increases the skeletal minion's Attack value by [color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 6. Increases the skeletal minion's Parry value by [color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 5. Increases the skeletal minion's Magic Resistance by [color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 8. Increases the skeletal minion's Strength by [color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 14. Allows an additional minion to be summoned every 2 levels up to a maximum of 5 minions. Cooldown changed from 7 seconds to 5 seconds. Range set to melee (self). Mana Cost set to 7. Does not naturally stack. [color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Control Undead:[/color] Takes control of a target Undead creature if the Priestess is not at her summoning limit, conferring half the bonuses that summoning would give from her Intelligence. Cooldown changed from 5 seconds to 4 seconds. Range set to 67% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 8. Does not naturally stack. [color:yellow]This sign contains detailed information on all non- Expansion Paladin spells[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Shield of Light:[/color] Increases the target's Armor, Dodge, Parry and Magic Resistance values. Armor gain changed from 4 to 1 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 7). Dodge gain changed from 10 to 6 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 4). Parry gain changed from 10 to 6 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 4). Magic Resistance gain changed from 15 to 9 + ([color:BCBCFF]Intelligence[/color] / 3). Duration reduced from 16.5 to 15 seconds. Cooldown reduced from 22 to 11 seconds. Range set to 50% of max cast range. Mana Cost set to 6. Can cast on allies. Does not naturally stack. [color:yellow]This sign contains detailed information on the Wizard's Fire Skill Tree[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Fire Bolt:[/color] Deals 5 - 7 [color: BDB76B]fire[/color] damage.[newline][color:808000]Required Level:[/color] 1[newline][color:808000]Prerequisite:[/color] None[newline][color:FAA460]Range:[/color] 70%[newline][color:light_blue]Mana Cost:[/color] 2[newline][color:878787]Cooldown:[/color] 1.2[newline][color:ADFF2F]Level Bonus:[/color] +2.5 Damage, +1 Mana Cost[newline][color:D2691E]Synergy Bonus:[/color][newline][color:DAA520] FireSurge:[/color] +10% Damage[newline][color:FF1493]Tier Bonus 1:[/color] Grants a 33% chance that no [color:light_blue]Mana[/color] is spent on the spell.[/color][color:C87DC8][newline][newline]Embers:[/color] Grants up to +1.25 [color:light_blue]Mana[/color] Regeneration as the Wizard's current [color:light_blue]Mana[/color] goes lower.[newline][color:808000]Required Level:[/color] 1[newline][color:808000]Prerequisite:[/color] None[newline][color:ADFF2F]Level Bonus:[/color] +0.75 Mana Regeneration[newline][color:D2691E]Synergy Bonus:[/color] None.[newline][color:FF1493]Tier Bonus 1:[/color] Increases HP regeneration as current [color:light_blue]Mana[/color] increases.[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]FireSurge:[/color] Deals 13 - 17 [color: BDB76B]fire[/color] damage in a small area around a single enemy target and reveals the area.[newline][color:808000]Required Level:[/color] 5[newline][color:808000]Prerequisite:[/color] Fire Bolt[newline][color:FAA460]Range:[/color] 80%[newline][color:FAA460]Radius:[/color] 75[newline][color:light_blue]Mana Cost:[/color] 6[newline][color:878787]Cooldown:[/color] 2.5[newline][color:ADFF2F]Level Bonus:[/color] +4 Damage, +5 Radius, +1.5 Mana Cost[newline][color:D2691E]Synergy Bonus:[/color][newline][color:DAA520] Fire Bolt:[/color] +8% Damage[newline][color:FF1493]Tier Bonus 1:[/color] Deals [color: BDB76B]fire[/color] damage over time to enemies in the area equal to 20% of this spell's damage per second for 3 seconds.[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Searing Mantle:[/color] Enchants the surface of a target with incredible heat, dealing 3 - 4 [color: BDB76B]fire[/color] damage whenever struck in melee combat and raises Armor by 1 and Fire Resistance by 10%.[newline][color:808000]Required Level:[/color] 5[newline][color:808000]Prerequisite:[/color] Fire Bolt[newline][color:FAA460]Range:[/color] 60%[newline][color:light_blue]Mana Cost:[/color] 8[newline][color:878787]Cooldown:[/color] 5[newline][color:ADFF2F]Level Bonus:[/color] +1 Damage, +0.5 Armor, +3% Fire Resistance, +4 Duration, +1 Mana Cost[newline][color:D2691E]Synergy Bonus:[/color] None.[newline][color:FF1493]Tier Bonus 1:[/color] Deals return damage to all attempted melee attacks.[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Ignite:[/color] Engulfs a target in flames, dealing 6 - 9 [color: BDB76B]fire[/color] damage per second for 7 seconds. Each second the target is on fire, nearby enemy units can also be caught on fire.[newline][color:808000]Required Level:[/color] 10[newline][color:808000]Prerequisite:[/color] None[newline][color:FAA460]Range:[/color] 75%[newline][color:FAA460]Radius:[/color] 50[newline][color:light_blue]Mana Cost:[/color] 15[newline][color:878787]Cooldown:[/color] 10[newline][color:ADFF2F]Level Bonus:[/color] +1.75 Damage, +6 Radius, +0.5 Duration, +2.25 Mana Cost[newline][color:D2691E]Synergy Bonus:[/color] None.[newline][color:FF1493]Tier Bonus 1:[/color] Can now spread to structures.[/color][color:C87DC8][newline][newline]Heatwave:[/color] Deals 9 - 11 [color: BDB76B]fire[/color] damage to enemies in an area around the Wizard each time he casts a spell.[newline][color:808000]Required Level:[/color] 10[newline][color:808000]Prerequisite:[/color] FireSurge[newline][color:FAA460]Radius:[/color] 80[newline][color:ADFF2F]Level Bonus:[/color] +2 Damage, +8 Radius[newline][color:D2691E]Synergy Bonus:[/color][newline][color:DAA520] Embers:[/color] +5% Damage[newline][color:DAA520] FireSurge:[/color] +7% Radius[newline][color:FF1493]Tier Bonus 1:[/color] Slightly knocks back all enemies damaged by Heatwave.[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Pyrelight:[/color] Marks a target enemy unit with bright light, reducing its [color: BDB76B]fire[/color] resistance by 20% for 30 seconds.[newline][color:808000]Required Level:[/color] 15[newline][color:808000]Prerequisite:[/color] Searing Mantle[newline][color:FAA460]Range:[/color] 85%[newline][color:light_blue]Mana Cost:[/color] 3[newline][color:878787]Cooldown:[/color] 5[newline][color:ADFF2F]Level Bonus:[/color] -4% Fire Resistance, +10 Duration, +0.5 Mana Cost[newline][color:D2691E]Synergy Bonus:[/color] None.[newline][color:FF1493]Tier Bonus 1:[/color] Enemies killed by spells while under Pyrelight restore the [color:light_blue]Mana[/color] used to cast it.[/color][color:FFBCFF][newline][newline]Perdition Barrage:[/color] Launches two projectiles at the approximate location of the target, dealing Deals 16 - 24 area of effect [color: BDB76B]fire[/color] damage and reveals the areas struck. The farther the target, the more random the end coordinates.[newline][color:808000]Required Level:[/color] 20[newline][color:808000]Prerequisite:[/color] FireSurge, Ignite[newline][color:FAA460]Range:[/color] 90%[newline][color:FAA460]Radius:[/color] 90[newline][color:FAA460]Random:[/color] 250[newline][color:light_blue]Mana Cost:[/color] 16[newline][color:878787]Cooldown:[/color] 8[newline][color:ADFF2F]Level Bonus:[/color] +6 Damage, +9 Radius, +12 Random, +3.25 Mana Cost[newline][color:D2691E]Synergy Bonus:[/color][newline][color:DAA520] Fire Bolt:[/color] +4% Damage[newline][color:DAA520] FireSurge:[/color] +7% Damage, +6% Radius[newli