Covers the history of arcane studies and how it culminated in the formation of the current-day Mage Guilds.[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]Experience: 1000[/color][color:DDBB44][newline]Level: 1[/color] Highlights the most renowned magical users known to the guild and their contributions to the development of magical study.[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]Experience: 1600[/color][color:DDBB44][newline]Level: 2[/color] Indicates the location of strong magical leylines in major guild locations as well as how to harness their potent energies to create a Wizards Guild.[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]Experience: 2500[/color][color:DDBB44][newline]Level: 3[/color] Contains excerpts and theories proposed by Brashnard on perpetuating magical enchantments on physical objects.[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]Experience: 3600[/color][color:DDBB44][newline]Level: 4[/color] Contains excerpts and theories proposed by Brashnard on perpetuating magical enchantments on physical objects.[color:BCFFBC][newline][newline]Experience: 4800[/color][color:DDBB44][newline]Level: 5[/color]
